This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. The paper also uses neural network models, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with subword representations, which are commonly used in neural machine translation, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with estimating out of vocabulary words, which is a common problem in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
